<item>
            <title>[LU-17358] jobstats output can produce invalid yaml ( part 3 )</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17358</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Given the following parms:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;jobid_name=%j@%u@%h
jobid_var=SLURM_JOB_ID&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And a job that does not have SLURM_JOB_ID set, it can product a job stats name along the lines of &quot;@4089401@host1&quot;.&#160; This will be printed unquoted by the current job_stats code.&#160; This is incorrect according to the YAML spec: &lt;a href=&quot;https://yaml.org/spec/1.2.2/#rule-c-reserved&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://yaml.org/spec/1.2.2/#rule-c-reserved&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
